      "stimulus_html": "",
      "stem_html": "<p>The dehydration of citrate to yield <i>cis</i>-aconitate, a step in the citric acid cycle, involves the pro-<i>R</i> “arm” of citrate rather than the pro-<i>S</i> arm. Which of the following two products is formed?</p>\n<img class=\"scaled-down\" src=\"https://exercises.openstax.org/rails/active_storage/blobs/proxy/eyJfcmFpbHMiOnsibWVzc2FnZSI6IkJBaHBBbzBSIiwiZXhwIjpudWxsLCJwdXIiOiJibG9iX2lkIn19--1c60eebcffd9a15a51b957a642806a6f93506ac3/OChem_05_EC_023.jpg\" alt=\"The figure shows a reaction where citrate converts to two forms of cis-aconitate structures.\">",
